# TASKS
## Phase 1: Foundation (Database & Config)
    Create MySQL database chat_app + Execute schema SQL for users and messages tables
    Create config/database.php with PDO connection + Write escape() helper function (htmlspecialchars wrapper)

## Phase 2: User Entry Point
    Build index.html with username form and chat container (initially hidden)
    Create api/login.php - validates username (no password), creates session
    Add JavaScript to show chat UI after login success

## Phase 3: Message Display & History
    Create api/history.php - returns last 50 messages JSON
    Write JS loadHistory() - fetches and displays messages
    Create style.css - chat bubbles, scrollable container

## Phase 4: Sending Messages
    Create api/send.php - expects POST {message}, inserts into DB
    Add message form to HTML with event listener + Write JS sendMessage() - POST to API, clear input
    Optimistic update: Add message to UI immediately, fallback on error

## Phase 5: Real-time Polling (Core Concept)
    Create api/poll.php - takes last_id param
    Logic: Query for messages > last_id, loop with usleep until found or timeout
    Write JS startPolling(lastMessageId) - recursive function
    Handle empty responses (no new messages)
    Add error handling with retry delay

## Phase 6: Polish & Edge Cases
    Auto-scroll to bottom on new messages
    Typing indicator (basic: on keypress → save to session, poll returns indicator)
    "User is typing..." (add typing_users table + cleanup cron)
    Disconnect detection (polling failure → show reconnecting)
    Rate limiting on send.php (max 5 messages per 10 seconds)
---
# Structure 
chat/
├── index.html          # Main chat interface
├── style.css           # Basic styling
├── js/
│   └── chat.js        # All frontend logic
├── api/
│   ├── login.php      # Set session
│   ├── send.php       # POST new message
│   ├── poll.php       # Long poll for new messages
│   └── history.php    # Get last 50 messages
├── config/
│   └── database.php   # DB connection
└── sql/
    └── setup.sql      # Database schema